title: CATER 154725, Kly Mod 30-3: KMC fault cleared.
text: Kly Mod 30-3: after LOTO, opened KMB box. All connections, wiring, and electronics good. Ohmed cable from trim supply DC output jacks to KMB: nothing shorted and ground wire good. Buttoned up KMB box. Energized trim supply: now have current to focus magnet and a reading off the KMB shunt: .0387 volts. Front panel of trim shows about 5 amps. Energized bulk supply. Still have Kly Mag Current fault on MKSU. Swapped cable of 30-3 PIOP module to PIOP of 30-2: fault on 30-3's MKSU goes away and 15 amps of current now energizing focus coil magnet. Swapped cables back on PIOP module and re-energized trim supply at 30-3: no more Kly Mag Current fault. Monitored current for several hours: no more faults. KMB shunt shows .1543 volts (X100 shunt). EPICs PIOP page shows 15.04 amps. If fault re-appears during ops, try IPLing PIOP and PIOP resets. If this doesn't clear fault, try re-seating PIOP CAMAC cable for station 30-3. After that, maybe PIOP module swap is in order. CATER ready to close. Thanks to Chief Master Tech Cordell Wilson for providing sound system knowledge in solving this issue. --chw, sj
